  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed roof extension, by reason of its scale, design, siting, excessive width, bulk, mass and fenestration would constitute and overly dominant and incongruous form of development, to the detriment of the architectural integrity of the host building and visual amenity and character of the surrounding area. The proposal would therefore fail to comply with the objectives of policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013), SPD4 and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021). | The proposed development by reason of insufficient internal floor area would result in a substandard form of accommodation to the detriment of the living conditions of future residents. The proposal would therefore be contrary to policies 3.5, 7B and 7D of the Development Management DPD (2013), Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021), The Technical Housing Standards and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021)."
